ding to this tale wherein the Teir'Dal maiden, finally touched with remorse, found a powerful cleric who was able to restore life to Valentine, and the two hunted together as one for the rest of their days.  And this is the reason that humans to this day, celebrate the festival of Valentine by giving each other symbols of the heart.<br><br>However, Teir'Dal know the true ending to the tale.  The Teir'Dal maid, in fact an accomplished practitioner of the dark arts, had obtained by voluntary sacrifice the heart of a paladin.  With this powerful reagent she was able to raise mighty forces, and devastated the mighty city that once stood in what is now the bare desert of North Ro (and of which the new town of Freeport is but a sad shadow).   She went on to many great victories in the name of Darkness, accompanied by a powerful undead minion obeying her every whim, who many said bore a marked resemblance to a certain paladin...  And this is the reason that Teir'Dal to this day, celebrate the festival of Valentine by giving each other symbols of the hearts of innocents.  For through the sacrifice of the inferior races will the glory of the Dark Lord come at last.<br><br>Praise be to Innoruuk, my tale is ended.<br><br>Lady Knight Didi<br>in the brotherhood of the League of Shadows<br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/upentapod.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pentapod</A> at: 2/17/02 9:53:31 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umaladominus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maladominus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 169<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/14/02 11:09:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=69.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Happy Valentine's Day</span><hr size=1> /applaud